    "narrative": "The offensive outlook for Ghost Ride the WHIP on April 11, 2026, centers on exploiting soft matchups against high-xERA starters. **Corbin Carroll** leads the charge with an elite 85.94 score; his combination of an 8% lineup order boost and a highly favorable matchup against Taijuan Walker makes him our clear cornerstone. We are also projecting significant upside from **Mickey Moniak** (75.98) and **Vinnie Pasquantino** (72.92). Both benefit from excellent SP skill projections\u2014+19% for each\u2014and dynamic platoon advantages against Erick Fedde and Germ\u00e1n M\u00e1rquez, respectively. **Josh Naylor** (71.88) rounds out our top tier, as his placement in the #4 hole against Lance McCullers Jr. ensures prime run-production opportunities in a favorable hitting environment.\n\nOur most difficult selection decision involved **Seiya Suzuki**, who missed the cut with a 50.78 score. While his park factors were positive, the optimizer downgraded his outlook due to the efficiency of Braxton Ashcraft and a suboptimal platoon situation. Consequently, he remains on the bench behind players like **Jazz Chisholm Jr.**, whose 69.72 score remains insulated by his aggressive base-running potential, a critical component given our team's emphasis on stolen bases. We are keeping a close watch on the \"Lineup Pending\" statuses for **Dalton Rushing**, **Jose Caballero**, **Max Muncy**, **Alex Freeland**, **Tyler Soderstrom**, **James Wood**, **Giancarlo Stanton**, and **Josh Naylor**. Any shifts in batting order\u2014specifically for **Dalton Rushing** or **Alex Freeland**\u2014could drastically impact their floor, as our current projections are highly sensitive to their expected #8 spots. Note that while **Corbin Carroll** is set for a strong day, he does face a slight efficiency drag from the opposing backstop, though his overall profile remains unmatched today.",
